 \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.eclipse.jetty.ee10:jetty-ee10-servlets:12.1.10\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Jetty EE10 utility servlets are separate from jetty-server and are referenced by existing 12.1.x metadata through webapp servlet configuration.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.eclipse.jetty.ee10:jetty-ee10-webapp:12.1.10\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Jetty EE10 WebAppContext and descriptor processing are separate optional modules and account for existing dynamic-access/resource metadata.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.eclipse.jetty.ee11:jetty-ee11-servlets:12.1.10\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Jetty EE11 utility servlets are separate from jetty-server and keep generation able to exercise the EE11 servlet/webapp stack.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.eclipse.jetty.ee11:jetty-ee11-webapp:12.1.10\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Jetty EE11 WebAppContext and descriptor processing are separate optional modules and are present in existing 12.1.x coverage.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Use embedded Jetty tests with a free local port and stop each Server in finally/cleanup. For WebAppContext native-image tests, register the resource URL scheme before startup with ResourceFactory.registerResourceFactory(\\\"resource\\\", new URLResourceFactory()), use a temporary base resource, and avoid EnvConfiguration/PlusConfiguration/JNDI unless intentionally testing them.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The added EE modules intentionally broaden the classpath beyond core jetty-server; generated tests should still stay scoped to Jetty server/servlet/webapp behavior already represented by the existing 12.1.x metadata.\",\n    \"Resource-scheme handling for webdefault/catalog resources can fail only in native-image even if JVM tests pass, so local Gradle and Native Image verification remain authoritative.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_06f7743e4da34840016a29fdc6c6688195b945097e2cd72b5c\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 33639, "output": 1084, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 34723, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1781136824123, "responseId": "resp_06f7743e4da34840016a29fdb90390819584eabfe6fea4cfb9"}}
